00:34:28.590 --> 00:34:30.570
Men work in Silicon Valley.

00:34:30.570 --> 00:34:32.739
They get paid very well.

00:34:32.739 --> 00:34:35.510
The income gap is very high.

00:34:35.510 --> 00:34:39.050
And that's the recipe.

00:34:39.050 --> 00:34:41.760
So we had this discussion
about dating in San Francisco.

00:34:41.760 --> 00:34:45.120
How many of you live
in San Francisco?

00:34:45.120 --> 00:34:50.179
So imagine a world in
which you have 101 women.

00:34:50.179 --> 00:34:51.580
It's a math problem.

00:34:51.580 --> 00:34:54.940
There's 101 women and 100 men.

00:34:54.940 --> 00:34:56.610
And we do this experiment.

00:34:56.610 --> 00:34:59.010
And we gave everybody $10.

00:34:59.010 --> 00:35:04.110
And we say, if at the end
of the game, you have money,

00:35:04.110 --> 00:35:07.310
you get to keep it as long as
you're paired with somebody

00:35:07.310 --> 00:35:09.360
of the opposition gender.

00:35:09.360 --> 00:35:11.820
So if you're a man and
woman, and you're paired up,

00:35:11.820 --> 00:35:13.780
you each get to keep your money.

00:35:13.780 --> 00:35:17.480
If you're not paired, the
money goes back to me.

00:35:17.480 --> 00:35:19.170
That's rule number one.

00:35:19.170 --> 00:35:23.100
And the second rule is
you could buy people.

00:35:23.100 --> 00:35:23.970
What does that mean?

00:35:23.970 --> 00:35:26.830
So let's say that Scott
and Logan are together,

00:35:26.830 --> 00:35:27.790
and I am alone.

00:35:27.790 --> 00:35:30.170
I can say, Logan, I have $10.

00:35:30.170 --> 00:35:35.402
If I give you $1, would
you drop Scott and join me?

00:35:35.402 --> 00:35:37.860
And the goal of the game is
not to be nice to your partner,

00:35:37.860 --> 00:35:39.160
the goal is to make money.

00:35:39.160 --> 00:35:40.560
So that's the goal.

00:35:40.560 --> 00:35:42.060
So let's say you switch to me.

00:35:42.060 --> 00:35:45.332
And then let's say Scott comes
and says he'll offer you $2.

00:35:45.332 --> 00:35:47.790
Now if you move to Scott, it's
not like an engagement ring.

00:35:47.790 --> 00:35:50.472
You don't get to keep my $1.

00:35:50.472 --> 00:35:51.430
You give it back to me.

00:35:51.430 --> 00:35:54.580
So at each point, if
you switch to somebody,

00:35:54.580 --> 00:35:57.120
you take what they gave you,
but the money you got before,

00:35:57.120 --> 00:35:58.660
you have to return.

00:35:58.660 --> 00:36:00.620
So now imagine the game.

00:36:00.620 --> 00:36:05.880
101 women, in total,
the women have $1,010.

00:36:05.880 --> 00:36:09.510
100 men, in total,
the men have $1,000.

00:36:09.510 --> 00:36:13.900
As the game continues,
at the end of the game,

00:36:13.900 --> 00:36:18.290
when nobody's switching anymore,
how much money do the men have?

00:36:18.290 --> 00:36:20.124
And how much money
do the women have?

00:36:22.760 --> 00:36:23.510
What do you think?

00:36:23.510 --> 00:36:24.570
So first of all,
who has more money?

00:36:24.570 --> 00:36:25.826
The men or the women?

00:36:25.826 --> 00:36:27.627
AUDIENCE: Women.

00:36:27.627 --> 00:36:28.210
DAN ARIELY: No

00:36:28.210 --> 00:36:30.580
AUDIENCE: Well, I'm
not from San Francisco,

00:36:30.580 --> 00:36:33.424
but it seems to me that if
you give them enough time

00:36:33.424 --> 00:36:35.478
to go back and
forth, the men will

00:36:35.478 --> 00:36:37.220
be left with next to nothing.

00:36:37.220 --> 00:36:38.650
DAN ARIELY: The men?

00:36:38.650 --> 00:36:39.990
No.

00:36:39.990 --> 00:36:43.920
So the result is
that the men end up

00:36:43.920 --> 00:36:46.060
with almost all the money.

00:36:46.060 --> 00:36:49.400
The women end up with $101.

00:36:49.400 --> 00:36:51.140
And the men end up
with everything.

00:36:51.140 --> 00:36:52.460
Why?

00:36:52.460 --> 00:36:55.080
So you have 100 men, 101 women.

00:36:55.080 --> 00:36:57.500
There's one woman alone.

00:36:57.500 --> 00:36:58.820
What does she do?

00:36:58.820 --> 00:37:00.580
She goes to a man
and says, hey, I'll

00:37:00.580 --> 00:37:02.160
give you $1 if you switch to me.

00:37:02.160 --> 00:37:03.200
The man switches.

00:37:03.200 --> 00:37:05.120
Now there's another
woman who's alone.

00:37:05.120 --> 00:37:06.750
She goes to another
man, another man.

00:37:06.750 --> 00:37:10.800
Eventually, all the men have
$11 and the women have $9.

00:37:10.800 --> 00:37:13.260
But there's still a
woman with no partner.

00:37:13.260 --> 00:37:14.300
So she continues.

