00:54:13.499 --> 00:54:14.040
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:54:14.040 --> 00:54:15.540
I would just like
to know if there's

00:54:15.540 --> 00:54:19.520
any sites and relationship
differences between regions

00:54:19.520 --> 00:54:22.490
where there's more tropical
weather, where you have more

00:54:22.490 --> 00:54:26.890
body exposure, and in places
where colder weather would

00:54:26.890 --> 00:54:27.890
have less body exposure.

00:54:27.890 --> 00:54:30.730
Because there's less
filling the gaps,

00:54:30.730 --> 00:54:33.290
leaving it to the
imagination, at least

00:54:33.290 --> 00:54:35.720
in a physical perspective.

00:54:35.720 --> 00:54:37.320
DAN ARIELY: Yeah,
so the site that

00:54:37.320 --> 00:54:40.530
leaves the least amount
of room for imagination

00:54:40.530 --> 00:54:43.250
is called Manhunt.

00:54:43.250 --> 00:54:46.230
I don't know if you've
been on that site,

00:54:46.230 --> 00:54:48.960
but it's really an amazing site.

00:54:51.530 --> 00:54:58.170
When we did this,
we did some work.

00:54:58.170 --> 00:55:01.620
So you know what's
called labor analysis?

00:55:01.620 --> 00:55:03.700
Labor analysis is
an analysis in which

00:55:03.700 --> 00:55:06.550
I take all your individual
characteristics-- your height,

00:55:06.550 --> 00:55:10.800
your weight, your education,
all kinds of things--

00:55:10.800 --> 00:55:13.460
and I regress it on your salary.

00:55:13.460 --> 00:55:16.050
And this is the kind of
research you do to find out

00:55:16.050 --> 00:55:17.540
what is the income gap.

00:55:17.540 --> 00:55:21.270
That men make more money
for the same job holding

00:55:21.270 --> 00:55:23.100
everything else equal.

00:55:23.100 --> 00:55:27.250
So we did the same
analysis for online dating.

00:55:27.250 --> 00:55:29.900
We said, let's look at you
and all your characteristics,

00:55:29.900 --> 00:55:33.980
and let's find what makes you
attractive in online dating.

00:55:33.980 --> 00:55:36.770
And one of the things we
found was that women really

00:55:36.770 --> 00:55:39.410
care about men's what?

00:55:39.410 --> 00:55:40.560
Height.

00:55:40.560 --> 00:55:42.920
Actually, tremendously so.

00:55:42.920 --> 00:55:45.210
So I'm 5' 9".

00:55:45.210 --> 00:55:48.140
If I wanted to be as successful
as somebody who is 5'

00:55:48.140 --> 00:55:51.270
10" in online dating,
how much more money

00:55:51.270 --> 00:55:53.510
would I have to make a year?

00:55:53.510 --> 00:55:56.053
What do you guess?

00:55:56.053 --> 00:55:58.510
AUDIENCE: $10,000.

00:55:58.510 --> 00:56:00.140
DAN ARIELY: It's about $40.

00:56:00.140 --> 00:56:02.230
It's about $40.

00:56:02.230 --> 00:56:04.700
Now just to be
clear, you can ask,

00:56:04.700 --> 00:56:08.230
are women really
that superficial?

00:56:08.230 --> 00:56:11.440
And the answer is yes and no.

00:56:11.440 --> 00:56:13.150
Partially, the
website, of course,

00:56:13.150 --> 00:56:15.630
gets women to search on height.

00:56:15.630 --> 00:56:18.450
So if you search and you say,
I want somebody who's 5' 10",

00:56:18.450 --> 00:56:21.350
you'll never see somebody who's
a real sweetheart but 5' 9".

00:56:21.350 --> 00:56:25.290
So sometimes, search
actually can take something

00:56:25.290 --> 00:56:29.920
that people have as a bias or as
a tendency, and exaggerate it.

00:56:29.920 --> 00:56:32.330
But anyway, women care
a lot about height.

00:56:32.330 --> 00:56:35.400
By the way, men care
a lot about BMI.

00:56:35.400 --> 00:56:37.910
And how much would
a woman with a BMI

00:56:37.910 --> 00:56:41.050
of, let's say 21, how
much more would she

00:56:41.050 --> 00:56:48.034
have to make to be as attractive
as a woman who has a BMI of 20?

00:56:48.034 --> 00:56:49.797
AUDIENCE: Nothing.

00:56:49.797 --> 00:56:51.880
DAN ARIELY: We can't
estimate it because men don't

00:56:51.880 --> 00:56:54.240
care how much money women make.

00:56:54.240 --> 00:56:57.120
Anyway, so this guy
called me up from Manhunt.

00:56:57.120 --> 00:57:01.680
And he said, look, the online
dating markets on Match

00:57:01.680 --> 00:57:05.180
or whatever it is
confuses two things.

00:57:05.180 --> 00:57:07.490
There's some people who are
there for the long term,

00:57:07.490 --> 00:57:09.590
and some people there
for the short term.

00:57:09.590 --> 00:57:11.740
And he said, let's
look at a website that

00:57:11.740 --> 00:57:14.700
just focuses on the short term.

00:57:14.700 --> 00:57:18.690
So he gave me his
password for Manhunt.

00:57:18.690 --> 00:57:22.970
And it's an amazing website
because they basically

00:57:22.970 --> 00:57:25.720
don't even show a picture
of the whole body.

00:57:25.720 --> 00:57:27.570
It's kind of-- uh.

00:57:30.615 --> 00:57:31.114
Um.

00:57:33.900 --> 00:57:37.975
So there are cultural
differences about what part

00:57:37.975 --> 00:57:39.790
you show.

00:57:39.790 --> 00:57:43.990
But I actually think it's
complex because it also

00:57:43.990 --> 00:57:46.320
shows something about
what kind of relationship

00:57:46.320 --> 00:57:50.054
you want, long-term, short-term,
other things like that as well.

